President Barack Obama has appointed Cassandra Q. Butts as Senior Advisor in the Office of the Chief Executive Officer at the Millennium Challenge Corporation. Butts is currently the Deputy White House Counsel and has previously served as the general counsel to the Obama-Biden Transition Project. She has also worked as the Senior Vice President for Domestic Policy at the Center for American Progress and as a senior advisor to House Democratic Leader Richard A. Gephardt. Butts brings a depth of experience and passion for justice that will be valuable to the Millennium Challenge Corporation's efforts in combating global poverty. President Obama expressed gratitude for Butts' service and looks forward to continuing to work with her in the future.